{"id": "EUVD-2022-55323", "enisaUuid": "744a50dc-76f0-381a-b0f3-989eb3b07fbe", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: Intel: avs: Fix potential buffer overflow by snprintf()\n\nsnprintf() returns the would-be-filled size when the string overflows\nthe given buffer size, hence using this value may result in a buffer\noverflow (although it's unrealistic).\n\nThis patch replaces it with a safer version, scnprintf() for papering\nover such a potential issue.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:45", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-13T21:31:18", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/840311a09f75632b9d41fbc1cd5c7aea94ce5f7e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ca3b7b9dc9bc1fa552f4697b7cccfa0258a44d00", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50052"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50052"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "007e5d55-1395-3d14-9e8f-ea3b31183194", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f1b3b320bd6519b16e3480f74f2926d106e3bcba <840311a09f75632b9d41fbc1cd5c7aea94ce5f7e"}, {"id": "3f749c58-8eaf-3232-abe7-6d83140e7c8a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.4"}, {"id": "54bcf96e-194c-3bb0-b73e-6be8e6f33678", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "95446496-98be-3c73-bc78-56b4c052a5ca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.19"}, {"id": "97a0e231-c956-346c-ab88-ffa1710b6899", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "d74560b7-4461-3a12-9a29-b719934c6f61", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f1b3b320bd6519b16e3480f74f2926d106e3bcba <ca3b7b9dc9bc1fa552f4697b7cccfa0258a44d00"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "ba9a400e-f7d0-36b9-ae53-9659590fda01", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}